9 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 16.1-01-15.1 of the North Dakota Century Code is
10 amended and reenacted as follows:
11 16.1-01-15.1. Use of nonpublic funds prohibited - Penalty.
12 1. The state and political subdivisions may not solicit, accept, or use any grants or
13 donations from private persons for elections operations or administration except:
14 a. The use of privately owned facilities for polling places;
15 b. Food for poll workers; and
16 c. Other nonmonetary donations that are not used to prepare, process, mark,
17 collect, or tabulate ballots or votes.
18 2. The state or any political subdivision of this state may not use a private entity for
19 election operations or administration to administer an election.
20 3. An individual who knowingly violates subsection 1 is guilty of a class A misdemeanor.
