1 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 16.1-06-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
2 amended and reenacted as follows:
3 16.1-06-02. Ballots prepared by county auditor or local official - Penalty.
4 For a local election, the ballots must be printed and distributed under the direction of the
5 auditor or clerk of the local subdivision. For all other elections, the secretary of state shall
6 prescribe a printer and ballots must be printed and distributed under the direction of the county
7 auditor, subject to the supervision and approval of the secretary of state as to the legal
8 sufficiency of the form, style, wording, and contents of the ballots. If an auditor or clerk of a local
9 subdivision, a county auditor, or the secretary of state causes or approves the printing of a
10 ballot listing an individual as a candidate when the official knows or should know the individual
11 does not meet the qualifications, or has not satisfied the requirements to be a candidate, the
12 official is guilty of an infraction.
13 SECTION 7. AMENDMENT. Subdivision g of subsection 1 of section 16.1-06-04 of the
14 North Dakota Century Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
15 g. Provide text boxes at the bottom of the first side of the ballot. The text box at the
16 bottom of the first column is to contain the words "Official Ballot, the name of the
17 county, the name or number of the precinct, and the date of the election". The
18 text box is to contain the words "All ballots, other than those used to vote
19 absentee, must first be initialed by appropriate election officials in order to be
20 counted". The text box at the bottom of the third column is to contain the word
21 "initials"phrase "election official initials" preceded by a blank line where the judge
22 or inspector shall initial the ballot.
